  <section>
    <title>Session Manager installation (sm.ulteo.com)</title>
    <para>
      Dependencies:
    </para>
    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem><para>Apache 2</para></listitem>
      <listitem><para>PHP 5 with curl, ldap, mysqlk modules</para></listitem>
      <listitem><para>MySQL</para></listitem>
    </itemizedlist>	  


    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
	<para>Download the software from <ulink url="ulteo-od.tar.gz" /></para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
	<para>Uncompress it in /tmp</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
	<para>place the sessionmanager directory in /var/www/sessionmanager</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
	<para>Donwload the application system archive from <ulink url="http://www.ulteo.com/main/downloads/ulteo-ovd.php" /></para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>

    <para>
      The server is now install but not configured. You can go to <ulink url="http://sm.ulteo.com/sessionmanager" /> with a web browser and you should see that page:
    </para>
  </section>


  <section>
    <title>Application server installation (cm.ulteo.com)</title>
    <para>
      Dependencies:
    </para>
    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem><para>Apache 2</para></listitem>
      <listitem><para>PHP 5 with curl support</para></listitem>
    </itemizedlist>	  


    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
	<para>Download the software from <ulink url="ulteo-od.tar.gz" /></para>
      </listitem>
     <listitem>
	<para>Uncompress it in /tmp</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
	<para>place the connectme directory in /var/www/connectme</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
	<para>Donwload the application system archive from your sessionmanager/base.tar.gz</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
	<para>Uncompress the base.tar.gz in /opt/connectme</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
	<para>Create a /etc/connectme.conf  and put "CHROOT=/opt/connectme"</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
	<para>Edit the /opt/connecme/etc/connectme.conf and specify SERVERNAME and SESSION_MANAGER_URL</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
	<para>chroot /opt/connectme /etc/init.d/connectmed</para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
  </section>
